events.name: Utah Jazz at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — Dennis Schröder hit the tying basket to force overtime and finished with 25 points, and the Los Angeles Lakers held off the Utah Jazz 127-115 on Saturday in a game between short-handed teams.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lakers hold off NBA-leading Jazz 127-115 in OT

headlines.description: — Russell Westbrook had his 25th triple-double of the season, Bradley Beal scored 37 points and the Washington Wizards beat the Detroit Pistons 121-100 on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Westbrook's triple-double, Beal's 37 lead Wiz over Pistons

headlines.description: — Nikola Vucevic scored 25 points, Lauri Markkanen added 16 off the bench and the Chicago Bulls beat the Cleveland Cavaliers 106-96 on Saturday night to snap a five-game losing streak.
headlines.shortLinkText: Bulls beat Cavs 106-96 to snap five-game skid

events.name: Golden State Warriors at Boston Celtics

headlines.description: — Jayson Tatum scored 44 points to win a shootout with Stephen Curry, who had 47, and Kemba Walker made a 3-pointer with 24 seconds left to lead the Boston Celtics to their sixth straight win, 119-114 over the Golden State Warriors on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Tatum (44) bests Curry (47), Celtics beat Warriors 119-114

headlines.description: — Grayson Allen shot 7 of 10 from 3-point range and scored 26 points to lead six Grizzlies in double figures as Memphis beat the Milwaukee Bucks 128-115 on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Grizzlies top Bucks 128-115 as they start fast on long trip

events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Phoenix Suns

headlines.description: — Rudy Gay scored 19 points, Drew Eubanks added 13 points and 13 rebounds in his first start of the season and the short-handed San Antonio Spurs had a surprisingly dominant 111-85 win over the Phoenix Suns on Saturday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Spurs win 111-85, stop Suns' 10-game home winning streak
